# Phase A вҖ” Stability / Health Hardening Spec

**Author:** Forge (KooshaPari planning)
**Status:** Draft, awaiting KooshaPari approval
**Date:** 2026-06-27
**Anchor:** `E:\plans\OmniRoute\2026-06-27-stability-first-reanchored.md`

The userвҖҷs stated intent in this turn was:

> "the main focus is not cost optimization, its stability/latency/health optimization to make requests stop failing so much in harnesses."

Phase A is the first PR cluster targeting that intent, designed to be the smallest possible surgical merge against `diegosouzapw/OmniRoute` with a feature flag, then completed with full E2E on the fork `KooshaPari/OmniRoute` before being proposed upstream.

---

## 1. Goal

Make a downstream harness (Cursor-style multi-turn coding, claude-code-style agents) able to issue hundreds of auto-routed requests with **near-zero transient failures caused by routing decisions themselves** вҖ” i.e., failures that are not legitimate provider errors but are caused by the router choosing a model that is mid-cooldown, has a hidden health regression, or is suffering a slow death while still appearing nominally healthy.

Specifically:

- Reduce the rate of routing-induced transient failures against `auto/*` and `combo:*` aliases from the current observable baseline to **< 0.5 percent** in the soak variant of `tests/e2e/system-failover.test.ts` over a 1h synthetic workload.
- Detect providers whose error rate is drifting upward in the **last 1 hour** even when their absolute failure rate is still nominally below the static lockout threshold.
- Surface a learned, per-(provider, model, error_class) failure rate to every existing router strategy without modifying those strategiesвҖҷ public interfaces.

## 2. Non-goals

- No change to provider auth flows, LiteLLM pricing sync, or quota subscription UI.
- No change to the public CLI / API contract (everything is feature-flagged off by default).
- No cost optimization beyond what falls out naturally (better failover вҮ’ fewer wasted premium-tier retries).

## 3. Pre-existing surface this builds on

Verified during this session (cited by file:line):

- `OmniRoute-upstream/open-sse/services/autoCombo/selfHealing.ts` вҖ” the 167-line class that today excludes providers below score 0.2, escalates cooldowns on repeated failures, and declares an incident if >= 50% are OPEN. This is the **only** existing health layer and it is purely in-memory and threshold-based.
- `OmniRoute-upstream/open-sse/services/autoCombo/scoring.ts` вҖ” the 6-factor scoring engine (quota, health, cost, latency, taskFit, stability). This spec adds a 7th factor `learnedFailureRate` and feeds it as an _additive_ input to the existing score, never replacing the static thresholds.
- `OmniRoute-upstream/open-sse/services/autoCombo/routerStrategy.ts:78-99` вҖ” pluggable `RouterStrategy` interface. No strategy is modified; the new `learningStrategy.ts` is added to the registry.
- `OmniRoute-upstream/src/domain/quotaCache.ts` вҖ” quota observation surface. The Phase 1 spec already adds an observer hook at `setQuotaCache()`. Phase A consumes that hookвҖҷs downstream `QuotaObservation` shape but does not own it.
- `OmniRoute-upstream/src/lib/db/migrations/097_model_intelligence.sql` вҖ” dormant-ish table for tiers/learned priors. Phase A adds a new sibling table `provider_health_history` rather than overloading it.
- `OmniRoute-upstream/open-sse/services/circuitBreaker/` вҖ” current circuit breaker (in-memory) that this spec complements but does not replace.

